# ============================================================
# CURSOR RULES — Master Chief's Stack
# Next.js · Tailwind · Supabase · Vercel · TypeScript
# shadcn/ui · Vercel AI SDK · Resend · Stripe
# ============================================================
# Every suggestion, edit, and generation must respect these rules.
# Do not deviate from this stack unless explicitly instructed.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. CORE STACK — NEVER SUGGEST ALTERNATIVES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Framework:        Next.js (App Router) with TypeScript
- Styling:          Tailwind CSS only
- UI Components:    shadcn/ui — always prefer existing primitives before building custom
- Database + Auth:  Supabase (Postgres + Supabase Auth)
- Deployment:       Vercel
- Language:         TypeScript everywhere — never plain JavaScript
- AI/LLM:           Vercel AI SDK + Anthropic (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)
- Forms:            react-hook-form + Zod
- Icons:            lucide-react only
- Animations:       framer-motion only
- Toasts:           sonner only
- Dates:            date-fns only
- Email:            Resend only
- Payments:         Stripe only
- i18n:             next-intl only
- URL State:        nuqs only
- Analytics:        Vercel Analytics + PostHog
- Error Tracking:   Sentry

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. DO NOT SUGGEST — EVER
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Redux, Zustand, Jotai (use React state + Server Components)
- Axios (use native fetch)
- Prisma, Drizzle, Mongoose (use Supabase client directly)
- Express or standalone Node servers (use Next.js API routes)
- Class components (functional only)
- styled-components, Emotion, CSS modules (use Tailwind)
- NextAuth, Clerk, Auth0 (use Supabase Auth)
- Firebase, PlanetScale (use Supabase)
- Nodemailer, SendGrid, Mailgun (use Resend)
- Any UI library other than shadcn/ui unless explicitly asked
- Pages Router (App Router only)
- Plain JavaScript files (TypeScript only)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. MIDDLEWARE & ROUTE PROTECTION
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Always use middleware.ts in the project root for auth route protection
- Use Supabase server client inside middleware to check session
- Define a matcher config — never run middleware on static assets or _next
- Protected routes redirect unauthenticated users to /login
- Public routes (landing, pricing, auth pages) must be explicitly whitelisted
- Never check auth inside individual page components — middleware handles this

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. URL STATE — NUQS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Use nuqs for all URL search param state — filters, pagination, search, tabs
- Never use useState for values that should be shareable or bookmarkable
- Always use parseAsInteger, parseAsString etc. for typed param parsing
- Combine with Server Components — pass searchParams from page.tsx down to components
- URL state is the source of truth for: search queries, active filters, current page, sort order

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. TOKEN EFFICIENCY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Never explain code changes unless explicitly asked
- Make surgical edits only — never rewrite an entire file for a small change
- Only comment non-obvious logic — skip self-evident comments
- Never justify stack choices mid-response
- Never touch code outside the scope of the request
- Skip preamble — go straight to the change

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. TYPESCRIPT
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Never use `any` — always define proper types or interfaces
- Use `type` for simple shapes, `interface` for component props
- Assume `"strict": true` in tsconfig
- Always type Supabase responses using generated DB types from `@/types/supabase`
- Let TypeScript infer where it safely can — don't over-annotate obvious types
- Always use path aliases — @/components, @/lib, @/types — never relative paths like ../../../

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. NEXT.JS APP ROUTER
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Always use the App Router (app/) — never the Pages Router
- Default to React Server Components (RSC)
- Add `"use client"` only when needed: useState, useEffect, event handlers, browser APIs
- Fetch data in Server Components — never useEffect for data fetching
- API routes live in app/api/[route]/route.ts using Web Request/Response API
- Use next/link for internal navigation, next/image for all images
- Use loading.tsx and error.tsx for loading and error states
- Public env vars: NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix; secret vars: no prefix, server only
- Use Next.js Metadata API for all SEO — every page exports a metadata object
- Lazy load heavy components with dynamic() to keep client bundles lean

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 8. TAILWIND CSS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Tailwind utility classes for ALL styling — no custom CSS unless unavoidable
- Use cn() (clsx + tailwind-merge) for all conditional class merging
- Mobile-first responsive design: base → sm → md → lg → xl
- Dark mode via Tailwind dark: variant only
- Stick to Tailwind's spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32...) — no arbitrary values like p-[13px]
- No hardcoded color hex values — use Tailwind's palette or shadcn CSS variables
- Text truncation: always use line-clamp-2 or line-clamp-3 on card headlines

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 9. SUPABASE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Server Components + API routes: use Supabase server client
- Client Components: use Supabase browser client
- Always destructure responses as { data, error } and handle both
- Row Level Security (RLS) always enabled — never disable it
- Use Supabase Storage for all file uploads — no local storage
- Full-text search via Supabase — always debounce inputs, show skeleton results
- Env vars: NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (server only)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 10. AI — VERCEL AI SDK + ANTHROPIC
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Always call AI from API routes — never from the client directly
- Use Vercel AI SDK's streamText for all streaming responses
- Default model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514
- Always set max_tokens — never leave it unbounded
- Store ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in .env.local — never hardcode or expose it
- Rate limit every AI route to protect against abuse and runaway costs

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 11. RESEND (EMAIL)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- All transactional emails go through Resend — no Nodemailer or SMTP
- Email sending always happens server-side in API routes only
- Use React Email templates for all email HTML — no raw HTML strings
- Always handle Resend errors gracefully — never let a failed email crash a flow
- Store RESEND_API_KEY in .env.local — never expose to client
- Always send from a verified domain — never from a generic address

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 12. STRIPE (PAYMENTS)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- All Stripe logic lives server-side — never trust client-side payment status
- Use Stripe webhooks to confirm payment success — never rely on redirect params
- Always verify webhook signatures using STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET
- Store STRIPE_SECRET_KEY server-side only; NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY for client
- Use Stripe Checkout or Payment Element — never build a custom card form
- Always handle idempotency — use Stripe idempotency keys for retries
- Update Supabase records only after confirmed webhook events — never before

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 13. FORMS — ZOD + REACT-HOOK-FORM
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Every form uses react-hook-form + zodResolver — no exceptions
- Define Zod schema first, infer the TypeScript type from it
- Always validate on both client (UX) and server (security) — never trust client alone
- Show inline field-level errors using shadcn FormMessage — no alert() or console errors
- Disable submit button while isSubmitting is true

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 14. PROJECT STRUCTURE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# app/                  → All routes and pages (App Router)
# app/api/              → API route handlers
# components/           → Reusable UI components
# components/ui/        → shadcn/ui primitives (never modify directly)
# lib/                  → Utility functions, helpers, constants
# lib/supabase/         → server.ts and client.ts Supabase clients
# lib/stripe/           → Stripe client setup
# lib/resend/           → Resend client and email templates
# types/                → Global TypeScript types
# types/supabase.ts     → Generated Supabase DB types
# public/               → Static assets only
# e2e/                  → Playwright end-to-end tests

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 15. NAMING CONVENTIONS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Components:         PascalCase (UserCard.tsx)
- Files/folders:      kebab-case (user-card.tsx, user-profile/)
- Functions/vars:     camelCase (getUserById)
- Constants:          SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_FILE_SIZE)
- Types/Interfaces:   PascalCase (UserProfile, ApiResponse)
- API routes:         kebab-case folders (app/api/send-email/route.ts)
- Zod schemas:        camelCase with Schema suffix (userFormSchema)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 16. CODE QUALITY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Keep components under ~100 lines — split if larger
- Prefer async/await over .then() chains
- Use early returns to avoid nesting
- Write descriptive variable names — no single-letter vars outside loops
- Import order: external libs → internal modules → components → types
- Git commits: conventional format — feat:, fix:, chore:, refactor:, docs:

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 17. ERROR & STATE HANDLING
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Always handle loading, error, and empty states — never just the happy path
- Loading: skeleton loaders for content, spinners only for action buttons
- Empty states: always show a helpful message or illustration when no data exists
- Errors: sonner toast for user-facing errors, Sentry for server-side logging
- Destructive actions (delete, cancel): always require a confirmation dialog first
- Never use console.log in production — use structured server-side logging only

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 18. SECURITY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Validate and sanitize all user input server-side with Zod before any processing
- Never trust client-side data — always re-validate on the server
- Cookies: always set httpOnly, secure, and sameSite flags
- Rate limit all API routes — especially AI, auth, and payment endpoints
- CORS: restrict API routes to your own domain only
- Add Content Security Policy headers in next.config.js
- SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY never sent to the client — ever
- .env.local must always be in .gitignore
- Never expose secrets in client-side code, logs, or error messages

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 19. UX & UI PATTERNS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Use shadcn Badge with defined variants for all status labels (Live, New, Breaking)
- Build reusable card components: image → label → headline → meta (always this order)
- Horizontal cards: aspect-video (16:9) — vertical/shorts: aspect-[9/16]
- Breadcrumbs on all nested pages using shadcn Breadcrumb component
- Footer must always include: Privacy Policy, Terms of Use, Accessibility links
- Gated content: blur overlay + CTA — never a hard redirect
- Semantic color usage: primary, secondary, destructive, muted — never ad hoc
- Relative timestamps using date-fns formatDistanceToNow ("2 hours ago")
- Optimistic UI: use useOptimistic for instant feedback on mutations — never wait for server response to update UI

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 20. TYPOGRAPHY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Always load fonts via next/font — never CDN links or CSS @import
- Stick to Tailwind's type scale only — no arbitrary sizes like text-[17px]
- Body text: leading-relaxed minimum at all times
- Long-form content: max-w-prose to cap reading width
- Card headlines: line-clamp-2; larger previews: line-clamp-3

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 21. IMAGES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Never use raw <img> tags — always next/image
- Always provide explicit width, height, and meaningful alt text
- Always use placeholder="blur" for graceful image loading
- Always define the sizes prop for responsive image delivery
- Configure next.config.js with all allowed image domains
- Every image container needs a fallback skeleton for slow or failed loads

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 22. ANIMATIONS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Use framer-motion for all animations — no ad hoc CSS keyframes
- Focus on high-impact moments: page load reveals, route transitions, hover states
- Keep animations subtle and purposeful — not decorative noise
- Always respect prefers-reduced-motion via framer-motion's useReducedMotion hook

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 23. INTERNATIONALISATION (i18n)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Use next-intl for all i18n — French is required (Canadian legal requirement)
- Never hardcode user-facing strings — always use translation keys
- RTL layout support via Tailwind rtl: variant for Arabic/Urdu if needed
- Always set the lang attribute on <html> dynamically based on locale

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 24. ANALYTICS & MONITORING
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Vercel Analytics: always included — add to root layout, zero config
- PostHog: custom event tracking — always initialize server-side
- Sentry: capture all unhandled server errors and API route exceptions
- Never log personal data (emails, names, IDs) in analytics events

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 25. TESTING
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Jest for unit tests — colocate as ComponentName.test.tsx
- Playwright for end-to-end tests — store in /e2e folder
- Write testable code: pure functions, small components, no side effects in renders
- Test files mirror source file names: user-card.tsx → user-card.test.tsx

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 26. ACCESSIBILITY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
- Always use semantic HTML (nav, main, article, section, header, footer)
- All interactive elements must be keyboard navigable
- Every image needs meaningful alt text — empty only if purely decorative
- ARIA labels on all icon-only buttons
- Minimum contrast: 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for large text

